<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
This native species is easily separated from all other 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Apioninae">Apioninae</taxonomicName>
known to occur in Quebec by the conspicuous elongate postscutellar spot of white vestiture and spot of dense white scales at the base of elytral interstriae 2 and 3. Nothing is known of its habits or life history, except that adults were collected in August on dock, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Rumex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rumex" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Rumex</taxonomicName>
L. spp., including golden dock, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Rumex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rumex persicarioides" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persicarioides">Rumex persicarioides</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName family="Polygonaceae" lsidName="" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" rank="family">Polygonaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Bright, DE" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Canada Publication 1882, Ottawa" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" title="The insects and arachnids of Canada. Part 21. The Weevils of Canada and Alaska. Volume 1. Coleoptera: Curculionoidea, excluding Scolytidae and Curculionidae." year="1993">Bright 1993</bibRefCitation>
). Ontario was until now considered as the eastward limit of its range in Canada (
<bibRefCitation author="Bousquet, Y" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" title="Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Second edition." year="2013">Bousquet et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). A photograph of one of the specimens reported herein is posted on bugguide.net (http://bugguide.net/node/view/1077586/bgpage).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
